6. There is a part `driver` of type `Driver`.
7. There is a part `vehicle` of type `Vehicle`.

10. The part `vehicle` contains a part `engine` of type `Engine`.

#### C. Event Occurrences (Interface/Behavior)
11. The part `driver` has an event occurrence `setSpeedSent`.
12. The part `vehicle.cruiseController` has an event occurrence `setSpeedReceived`.
13. The part `vehicle.cruiseController` has an event occurrence `sensedSpeedReceived`.
14. The part `vehicle.cruiseController` has an event occurrence `fuelCommandSent`.
15. The part `vehicle.speedometer` has an event occurrence `sensedSpeedSent`.
16. The part `vehicle.engine` has an event occurrence `fuelCommandReceived`.

#### D. Item Definitions (Messages/Data Types)
17. There is an item type `SetSpeed`.
18. There is an item type `SensedSpeed`.
19. There is an item type `FuelCommand`.

#### E. Occurrence Definition (Interaction/Protocol)
20. There is an occurrence type `CruiseControlInteraction` that references `driver` and `vehicle` parts.
21. There is a message `setSpeedMessage` of type `SetSpeed` from `driver.setSpeedSent` to `vehicle.cruiseController.setSpeedReceived`.
22. There is a message `sensedSpeedMessage` of type `SensedSpeed` from `vehicle.speedometer.sensedSpeedSent` to `vehicle.cruiseController.sensedSpeedReceived`.
23. There is a message `fuelCommandMessage` of type `FuelCommand` from `vehicle.cruiseController.fuelCommandSent` to `vehicle.engine.fuelCommandReceived`.
24. The protocol specifies the order: first `setSpeedMessage`, then `sensedSpeedMessage`.

#### F. Instance Declarations (Behavioral Realization)
25. There is a part `driver_a` of type `Driver` with an action `driverBehavior` that sends `SetSpeed` to `vehicle_a`.
26. There is a part `vehicle_a` of type `Vehicle`.

    - `receiveSensedSpeed` accepts `SensedSpeed` via `cruiseController_a`.
    - `sendFuelCommand` sends `FuelCommand` to `engine_a`.
28. The part `vehicle_a` contains a part `speedometer_a` of type `Speedometer` with action `sendSensedSpeed` sends `SensedSpeed` to `cruiseController_a`.
29. The part `vehicle_a` contains a part `engine_a` of type `Engine` with action `receiveFuelCommand` accepts `FuelCommand` via `engine_a`.

#### G. Occurrence Instance (Interaction Realization)
30. There is an occurrence `cruiseControlInteraction_a` of type `CruiseControlInteraction` that maps the above parts and events to the protocol.
31. The occurrence instance maps the messages to the sent messages in the behaviors.
